		"body": "On Linux, pasting a JPEG image from the system clipboard into a Joplin note does nothing. The image is silently dropped. PNG paste works fine, and drag-and-dropping a JPEG file also works. Only JPEG clipboard paste is broken.\r\n\r\n## The problem\r\n\r\nTwo Electron/Chromium platform behaviours combine to break this:\r\n\r\n1. `clipboard.availableFormats()` returns `[]` for JPEG-only clipboard data on Linux, even though the JPEG bytes are present. This is a known Chromium limitation ([electron/electron#32490](https://github.com/electron/electron/issues/32490)). Since the old code iterated over `availableFormats()`, the loop body never executed for JPEG.\r\n\r\n2. `clipboard.readImage()` returns an empty `NativeImage` for JPEG-only clipboard data, so even if the format were detected, the old `readImage()` to `nativeImage.toJPEG()` path would produce a corrupt file.\r\n\r\n## The fix\r\n\r\nReplace the detection and reading strategy in `getResourcesFromPasteEvent`:\r\n\r\n| Before                                             | After                                                             |\r\n| -------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |\r\n| `clipboard.availableFormats()` to detect formats   | `clipboard.has(format)` against a fixed list of supported formats |\r\n| `clipboard.readImage()` to read image data         | `clipboard.readBuffer(format)` to read raw bytes                  |\r\n| `shim.writeImageToFile()` (NativeImage conversion) | `shim.fsDriver().writeFile()` (write buffer directly)             |\r\n| `event.preventDefault()` called before attachment  | `event.preventDefault()` called only after successful attachment  |\r\n\r\n`clipboard.has()` and `clipboard.readBuffer()` work correctly on all platforms (Linux, macOS, Windows), so the fix is applied unconditionally rather than behind a platform check.\r\n\r\nThe function signature and return type are unchanged. All three callers (TinyMCE, CodeMirror v5, CodeMirror v6) work without modification.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n### Automated\r\n\r\nAll 11 tests pass in `resourceHandling.test.ts` (7 existing + 4 new).\r\n\r\n### Manual\r\n\r\n1. Copied JPEG via `xclip -selection clipboard -t image/jpeg test.jpeg`, pressed Ctrl+V in Joplin. Image appears in note.\r\n2. Copied PNG via `xclip -selection clipboard -t image/png test.png`, pressed Ctrl+V. Image appears in note.\r\n3. Copied image from browser (right-click, Copy Image), pressed Ctrl+V. Image appears in note.\r\n4. Pasted plain text. Text appears normally, no interference.\r\n5. Tested in both Rich Text (TinyMCE) and Markdown (CodeMirror) editors.\r\n\r\n### Video\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/35c109d0-aec0-486d-80e1-d6ff66cae87f\r\n\r\n## AI Assistance Disclosure\r\n\r\nThis PR used AI to assist with code refactoring and test design. All code has been manually reviewed and tested.\r\n",
